Key Match Events: Namibia clinched a thrilling Super Over win against Oman to kick off their T20 World Cup campaign at the Kensington Oval.
Ruben Trumpelmann made history by becoming the first player in T20I history to take two wickets with the first two balls of a match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the second Super Over in T20 World Cup history, following the first-ever between New Zealand and Sri Lanka in Kandy in 2012.
Others: Jan Frylinck anchored the innings with a steady 45 off 48 balls, but Mehran Khan's exceptional bowling (3/7) kept the pressure on Namibia.
David Wiese took responsibility with the ball as well, claiming 3/28.
